 **🔎 Key Findings**
-> Customers within the first 6 months show the highest churn rate.
-> Low-usage customers are significantly more likely to churn (up to 3x higher).
-> Customers with frequent support interactions exhibit higher churn, indicating dissatisfaction.
-> Premium plan users show unexpectedly higher churn compared to other plans.

 **💡 Recommendations**
-> Improve the onboarding experience to retain early-stage customers.
-> Launch targeted engagement campaigns for low-usage users.
-> Enhance customer support quality and resolution time.
-> Promote long-term (annual) subscription plans with incentives.

Addressing these factors can significantly reduce churn and improve long-term customer retention and revenue stability.
